 widespread and can be\ndetected within modest-redshift lensed galaxies so that the luminosity distance\nis not prohibitive for detecting individual magnified stars. Continuous {\\it\nHubble Space Telescope} monitoring of several such optimal arcs will be\nrewarded by an unprecedented mass spectrum of compact objects that can\ncontribute to uncovering the nature of dark matter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Jun 2017 17:25:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 23 Mar 2018 23:40:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-25"}
